Knit 2, slip 2 stitches onto the cable needle and hold in back, knit 2, knit 2 stitches of cable needle, knit 2. Knit 2, purl 4, knit 2. Knit 8. Knit 2, purl 4, knit 2. Knit 8. Knit 2, purl 4, knit 2. Knit 8. Knit 2, purl 4, knit 2. Or use the internet to find your own! Repeat your stitch pattern until it measures from one ear lobe to the other across the top of your head. Remember to stretch the yarn while fitting. Decrease until you have the correct number of stitches for your i-cord. For example if you had eight stitches, knit one, knit two together, knit one, knit two together, knit one, knit two together. Purl the wrong side and continue in a similar fashion until you have for example, three stitches left. See Knit Decreases to learn how. Knit the i-cord until it measures a little longer than the distance from behind your other ear to the nape of your neck.  Bind off and break the yarn. Leave approximately 3-4 inches (7.5cm to 10cm) of tail yarn on this end as well. Use a darning needle to thread the end of the tail yarn into the i-cord from its end. Pull it out some distance along the i-cord, pull it so it's very taunt and snip it. Then pull at the i-cord so that the yarn end shrinks into the i-cord. Repeat this at the other end. Wear your fabulous headband! Wrap it around your head, making sure the right side is facing outwards, and tie the i-cords together at the nape of your neck in a square knot.
